The paper deals with semantic segmentation of surgical instruments, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions robot-assisted surgery, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.RO (Robotics). The attention module proposed in the paper is a novel contribution, which could be of interest to researchers in cs.MM (Multimedia). The hybrid loss function introduced in the paper is a combination of cross-entropy and Dice loss, which are commonly used in deep learning for segmentation tasks, indicating that the paper could be relevant to researchers in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
